        Explore Batches →
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════
     FAQs
══════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="faqs" class="py-16 px-6">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="reveal mb-12 text-center">
      <p class="text-purple-400 text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">Common Questions</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-4xl font-800 text-white">DILR Test FAQs</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      {[
        { q: "Are these DILR sectional tests free?", a: "Yes — all 4 DILR tests are completely free with no signup fee. Click any 'Start Test' button to begin immediately." },
        { q: "How many sets are in each DILR test?", a: "Each test has 4 sets — 2 DI sets and 2 LR sets — with 5 questions each, totalling 20 questions. This matches the actual CAT DILR section structure." },
        { q: "What types of sets are covered?", a: "Across the 4 tests we cover bar charts, pie charts, line graphs, caselets, seating arrangements, scheduling, blood relations, grid puzzles, Venn diagrams, tournament brackets and novel-format sets." },
        { q: "Is DILR scoring different from other sections?", a: "Scoring follows the same CAT pattern: +3 for correct MCQs, -1 for wrong MCQs, and no negative marking for TITA questions. Our tests replicate this exactly." },
        { q: "Can I skip sets inside a test?", a: "Yes — like the real CAT, you can navigate between questions freely and flag questions to return to. Developing a skip-and-return strategy is part of what these tests train." },
        { q: "Will I get explanations for each set?", a: "Yes — complete solutions with approach explanation and optimal solving sequence are provided immediately after submission." },
      ].map((faq, i) => (
        <div class="reveal glass rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
          <button class="faq-btn w-full text-left px-7 py-5 flex items-start justify-between gap-4" data-index={i}>
            <span class="font-display font-700 text-white text-sm leading-relaxed">{faq.q}</span>
            <span class="faq-icon text-purple-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 text-lg">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-body hidden px-7 pb-6">
            <p class="text-ink-200 text-sm leading-relaxed">{faq.a}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════
     FOOTER
══════════════════════════════ -->
<footer class="border-t border-white/06 bg-ink-900 pt-16 pb-8 px-6">
